<!DOCTYPE html> //always right at the top and tells browser looking at HTML file 

<html>
<head> // extra information that doesnt show up on screen

    <meta charset= "utf-8"> <!-- ensures that the webpage will display special characters and symbols from diff languages -->

    <title> my first website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">

<body style="background-color:#000; color:#FFF;">// content that user sees 
    <h1> Welcome!</h1>

    <h2 style="color:rgb(93, 178, 248); font-size:40px;";> This is to change color! </h2>
s
    <strong> Makes things bold </strong>


    <em> Makes things italic. Stands for emphasis</em>

    <!--> This is an HTML comment. Only notes to yourself.  
        b and i does not add meaning to text only bolds and italics do not use  -->

    <a href="http://www.google.com "> this will link you to google. This is an absolute link</a>

    <p style="color: blueviolet; font-size:20px; font-family: sans-serif;">My first website! Hi gaiz!</p>

    <p> very cool! The p tag makes new paragraphs </p>


    <div> I am inside a div. This helps separate. It stands for divide. </div>
    <div> this is a second div. We use classes to organize layout. Class is the name 
        of the div and we want it to be descriptive.  </div>

    <div class="top-section"> we want the name to be descriptive. we use period to 
        signify class
    </div>

    <span class="hightlight"> just to use for different properties </span>

    <div id="specific"> an ID is very specific and can only have one per. Unique. </div>

